                                IHelp

        IHelp assigns keys on keyboard to functions usually carried out by
the mouse. Double-click on the IHelp icon to start it. The operations
performed by IHelp and the default keyboard assignments are as follows:

        Cycle windows The default key is F1. Pressing this key activates
the rearmost application window on the Workbench screen and brings it to 
the front. This does not affect windows for drawers and disks, only
applications such as the Clock or the Calculator.

        Enlarge window The default key is F2, The Active window is enlarged
to its maximum size.

        Shrink  window The default key is F3. The active window is shrunk
to its minimum size.

        Cycle screens The default key is F4. The rearmost screen is brought
to the front.

        Zoom window The default key is F5. Zooms the active window, just as
if you had clicked on the window's zoom gadget with the mouse.

        To exit IHelp, double click on its icon again or use the Exchange
program (see Utilities/Exchange) to Kill it.


